<p><b>Charles Tilly</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1929-05-27"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="05-27"><a href="/wiki/May_27" title="May 27">May 27</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1929" title="1929">1929</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-04-29"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="04-29"><a href="/wiki/April_29" title="April 29">April 29</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a></span><sup id="cite_ref-death_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-death-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>) was an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Sociology" title="Sociology">sociologist</a>, <a href="/wiki/Political_science" title="Political science">political scientist</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Historian" title="Historian">historian</a> who has written books on the relationship between <a href="/wiki/Politics" title="Politics">politics</a> and <a href="/wiki/Society" title="Society">society</a>.</p>
